    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1968-11-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1968-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="81"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                <head>81. Letter From President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1" type="from"
                        >Johnson</persName> to the Chairman of the President’s Advisory Committee on
                    Foreign Assistance Programs (<persName corresp="#p_PJA3" type="to"
                        >Perkins</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d81fn1">Source:
                        Johnson Library, <persName corresp="#p_FER1">Edward R. Fried</persName>
                        Files, <hi rend="italic">Chron</hi> File, Box 3. No classification marking.
                        Drafted by President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_FER1">Edward R. Fried</persName>, and
                            <persName>Roger P. Morris</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian"
                            notAfter="1968-11-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                            notBefore="1968-11-01T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Dear <persName>Jim</persName>:</p>
                <p>Many thanks for your letter enclosing your Committee’s final report on
                    development assistance.<note n="2" xml:id="d81fn2">See <ref target="#d79"
                            >Document 79</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I know that a great deal of time, talent, and hard work went into this effort.
                    You and your distinguished colleagues have performed a valuable public
                    service—in the interest of our own security and of the hopes of millions of
                    people around the world who seek a better life.</p>
                <p>I have asked Secretary <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName>, Secretary
                        <persName corresp="#p_CCM2">Clifford</persName>, Aid Administrator <persName
                        corresp="#p_GWS1">Gaud</persName> and Budget Director <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZCJ2">Zwick</persName> to go over your proposals and give me <pb
                        facs="0266" n="232" xml:id="pg_232"/> their comments. I will be most pleased
                    to pass on the Committee’s report and our appraisal of it to the next
                    Administration. I believe it will be an important contribution to the
                    deliberations ahead on the future of foreign aid.</p>
                <p>I deeply appreciate your personal leadership in the work of the Committee.</p>
                <p>With warm personal regards,</p>
                <p>Sincerely,<note n="3" xml:id="d81fn3">Printed from an unsigned copy.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
